23/03/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- The left-wing guerrilla group Conspiracy Nuclei of Fire on Monday (March 22nd) claimed responsibility for three bombings in Athens last week that caused minor damage but no injuries. Two of the blasts occurred on Saturday, targeting a police detention centre and the home of a leading member of the Pakistani community. On Friday, a bomb damaged the office of an ultra-nationalist group in downtown Athens. Police are investigating the authenticity of the group's claims. 
In other news, the union representing public employees, ADEDY, is organising another demonstration Tuesday in downtown Athens, against the government's austerity measures. (Focus - 23/02/10; Kathimerini, Reuters, AP, DPA - 22/03/10)
